{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":3000,"text":"I wrote a letter last week talking about the work of the foundation,"},{"time":6000,"text":"sharing some of the problems."},{"time":9000,"text":"And Warren Buffet had recommended I do that --"},{"time":12000,"text":"being honest about what was going well, what wasn't,"},{"time":15000,"text":"and making it kind of an annual thing."},{"time":18000,"text":"A goal I had there was to draw more people in to work on those problems,"},{"time":21000,"text":"because I think there are some very important problems"},{"time":24000,"text":"that don't get worked on naturally."},{"time":27000,"text":"That is, the market does not drive the scientists,"},{"time":32000,"text":"the communicators, the thinkers, the governments"},{"time":35000,"text":"to do the right things."},{"time":38000,"text":"And only by paying attention to these things"},{"time":41000,"text":"and having brilliant people who care and draw other people in"},{"time":45000,"text":"can we make as much progress as we need to."}]},{"cues":[{"time":47000,"text":"So this morning I'm going to share two of these problems"},{"time":50000,"text":"and talk about where they stand."},{"time":53000,"text":"But before I dive into those I want to admit that I am an optimist."},{"time":57000,"text":"Any tough problem, I think it can be solved."},{"time":61000,"text":"And part of the reason I feel that way is looking at the past."},{"time":64000,"text":"Over the past century, average lifespan has more than doubled."},{"time":69000,"text":"Another statistic, perhaps my favorite,"},{"time":72000,"text":"is to look at childhood deaths."},{"time":75000,"text":"As recently as 1960, 110 million children were born,"},{"time":81000,"text":"and 20 million of those died before the age of five."},{"time":85000,"text":"Five years ago, 135 million children were born -- so, more --"},{"time":89000,"text":"and less than 10 million of them died before the age of five."},{"time":95000,"text":"So that's a factor of two reduction of the childhood death rate."},{"time":100000,"text":"It's a phenomenal thing."},{"time":102000,"text":"Each one of those lives matters a lot."}]},{"cues":[{"time":105000,"text":"And the key reason we were able to it was not only rising incomes"},{"time":110000,"text":"but also a few key breakthroughs:"},{"time":113000,"text":"vaccines that were used more widely."},{"time":116000,"text":"For example, measles was four million of the deaths"},{"time":119000,"text":"back as recently as 1990"},{"time":121000,"text":"and now is under 400,000."},{"time":124000,"text":"So we really can make changes."},{"time":126000,"text":"The next breakthrough is to cut that 10 million in half again."},{"time":130000,"text":"And I think that's doable in well under 20 years."},{"time":134000,"text":"Why? Well there's only a few diseases"},{"time":138000,"text":"that account for the vast majority of those deaths:"},{"time":141000,"text":"diarrhea, pneumonia and malaria."}]},{"cues":[{"time":147000,"text":"So that brings us to the first problem that I'll raise this morning,"},{"time":152000,"text":"which is how do we stop a deadly disease that's spread by mosquitos?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":159000,"text":"Well, what's the history of this disease?"},{"time":161000,"text":"It's been a severe disease for thousands of years."},{"time":164000,"text":"In fact, if we look at the genetic code,"},{"time":167000,"text":"it's the only disease we can see"},{"time":170000,"text":"that people who lived in Africa"},{"time":172000,"text":"actually evolved several things to avoid malarial deaths."},{"time":176000,"text":"Deaths actually peaked at a bit over five million in the 1930s."},{"time":182000,"text":"So it was absolutely gigantic."},{"time":185000,"text":"And the disease was all over the world."},{"time":188000,"text":"A terrible disease. It was in the United States. It was in Europe."},{"time":191000,"text":"People didn't know what caused it until the early 1900s,"},{"time":194000,"text":"when a British military man figured out that it was mosquitos."},{"time":200000,"text":"So it was everywhere."},{"time":202000,"text":"And two tools helped bring the death rate down."},{"time":206000,"text":"One was killing the mosquitos with DDT."},{"time":209000,"text":"The other was treating the patients with quinine, or quinine derivatives."},{"time":214000,"text":"And so that's why the death rate did come down."}]},{"cues":[{"time":218000,"text":"Now, ironically, what happened was"},{"time":221000,"text":"it was eliminated from all the temperate zones,"},{"time":224000,"text":"which is where the rich countries are."},{"time":225000,"text":"So we can see: 1900, it's everywhere."},{"time":227000,"text":"1945, it's still most places."},{"time":231000,"text":"1970, the U.S. and most of Europe have gotten rid of it."},{"time":234000,"text":"1990, you've gotten most of the northern areas."},{"time":237000,"text":"And more recently you can see it's just around the equator."}]},{"cues":[{"time":243000,"text":"And so this leads to the paradox that"},{"time":247000,"text":"because the disease is only in the poorer countries,"},{"time":249000,"text":"it doesn't get much investment."},{"time":253000,"text":"For example, there's more money put into baldness drugs"},{"time":257000,"text":"than are put into malaria."},{"time":260000,"text":"Now, baldness, it's a terrible thing."},{"time":263000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":266000,"text":"And rich men are afflicted."},{"time":269000,"text":"And so that's why that priority has been set."}]},{"cues":[{"time":275000,"text":"But, malaria --"},{"time":277000,"text":"even the million deaths a year caused by malaria"},{"time":279000,"text":"greatly understate its impact."},{"time":281000,"text":"Over 200 million people at any one time are suffering from it."},{"time":284000,"text":"It means that you can't get the economies in these areas going"},{"time":289000,"text":"because it just holds things back so much."},{"time":292000,"text":"Now, malaria is of course transmitted by mosquitos."},{"time":296000,"text":"I brought some here, just so you could experience this."},{"time":301000,"text":"We'll let those roam around the auditorium a little bit."},{"time":305000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":308000,"text":"There's no reason only poor people should have the experience."},{"time":311000,"text":"(Laughter) (Applause)"},{"time":318000,"text":"Those mosquitos are not infected."}]},{"cues":[{"time":323000,"text":"So we've come up with a few new things. We've got bed nets."},{"time":327000,"text":"And bed nets are a great tool."},{"time":330000,"text":"What it means is the mother and child stay under the bed net at night,"},{"time":333000,"text":"so the mosquitos that bite late at night can't get at them."},{"time":338000,"text":"And when you use indoor spraying with DDT"},{"time":343000,"text":"and those nets"},{"time":344000,"text":"you can cut deaths by over 50 percent."},{"time":347000,"text":"And that's happened now in a number of countries."},{"time":350000,"text":"It's great to see."}]},{"cues":[{"time":352000,"text":"But we have to be careful because malaria --"},{"time":355000,"text":"the parasite evolves and the mosquito evolves."},{"time":360000,"text":"So every tool that we've ever had in the past has eventually become ineffective."},{"time":364000,"text":"And so you end up with two choices."},{"time":367000,"text":"If you go into a country with the right tools and the right way,"},{"time":371000,"text":"you do it vigorously,"},{"time":374000,"text":"you can actually get a local eradication."},{"time":377000,"text":"And that's where we saw the malaria map shrinking."},{"time":379000,"text":"Or, if you go in kind of half-heartedly,"},{"time":382000,"text":"for a period of time you'll reduce the disease burden,"},{"time":385000,"text":"but eventually those tools will become ineffective,"},{"time":389000,"text":"and the death rate will soar back up again."},{"time":392000,"text":"And the world has gone through this where it paid attention and then didn't pay attention."}]},{"cues":[{"time":397000,"text":"Now we're on the upswing."},{"time":399000,"text":"Bed net funding is up."},{"time":402000,"text":"There's new drug discovery going on."},{"time":405000,"text":"Our foundation has backed a vaccine that's going into phase three trial"},{"time":409000,"text":"that starts in a couple months."},{"time":410000,"text":"And that should save over two thirds of the lives if it's effective."},{"time":413000,"text":"So we're going to have these new tools."}]},{"cues":[{"time":416000,"text":"But that alone doesn't give us the road map."},{"time":419000,"text":"Because the road map to get rid of this disease"},{"time":422000,"text":"involves many things."},{"time":424000,"text":"It involves communicators to keep the funding high,"},{"time":427000,"text":"to keep the visibility high,"},{"time":429000,"text":"to tell the success stories."},{"time":431000,"text":"It involves social scientists,"},{"time":433000,"text":"so we know how to get not just 70 percent of the people to use the bed nets,"},{"time":436000,"text":"but 90 percent."},{"time":438000,"text":"We need mathematicians to come in and simulate this,"},{"time":441000,"text":"to do Monte Carlo things to understand how these tools combine and work together."},{"time":447000,"text":"Of course we need drug companies to give us their expertise."},{"time":450000,"text":"We need rich-world governments to be very generous in providing aid for these things."},{"time":455000,"text":"And so as these elements come together,"},{"time":458000,"text":"I'm quite optimistic"},{"time":461000,"text":"that we will be able to eradicate malaria."}]},{"cues":[{"time":465000,"text":"Now let me turn to a second question,"},{"time":468000,"text":"a fairly different question, but I'd say equally important."},{"time":472000,"text":"And this is: How do you make a teacher great?"},{"time":475000,"text":"It seems like the kind of question that people would spend a lot of time on,"},{"time":480000,"text":"and we'd understand very well."},{"time":483000,"text":"And the answer is, really, that we don't."},{"time":487000,"text":"Let's start with why this is important."},{"time":490000,"text":"Well, all of us here, I'll bet, had some great teachers."},{"time":494000,"text":"We all had a wonderful education."},{"time":497000,"text":"That's part of the reason we're here today,"},{"time":500000,"text":"part of the reason we're successful."},{"time":502000,"text":"I can say that, even though I'm a college drop-out."},{"time":505000,"text":"I had great teachers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":508000,"text":"In fact, in the United States, the teaching system has worked fairly well."},{"time":513000,"text":"There are fairly effective teachers in a narrow set of places."},{"time":518000,"text":"So the top 20 percent of students have gotten a good education."},{"time":521000,"text":"And those top 20 percent have been the best in the world,"},{"time":525000,"text":"if you measure them against the other top 20 percent."},{"time":528000,"text":"And they've gone on to create the revolutions in software and biotechnology"},{"time":533000,"text":"and keep the U.S. at the forefront."}]},{"cues":[{"time":537000,"text":"Now, the strength for those top 20 percent"},{"time":540000,"text":"is starting to fade on a relative basis,"},{"time":543000,"text":"but even more concerning is the education that the balance of people are getting."},{"time":549000,"text":"Not only has that been weak. it's getting weaker."},{"time":554000,"text":"And if you look at the economy, it really is only providing opportunities now"},{"time":558000,"text":"to people with a better education."},{"time":561000,"text":"And we have to change this."},{"time":564000,"text":"We have to change it so that people have equal opportunity."},{"time":567000,"text":"We have to change it so that the country is strong"},{"time":570000,"text":"and stays at the forefront"},{"time":572000,"text":"of things that are driven by advanced education,"},{"time":575000,"text":"like science and mathematics."}]},{"cues":[{"time":577000,"text":"When I first learned the statistics,"},{"time":580000,"text":"I was pretty stunned at how bad things are."},{"time":583000,"text":"Over 30 percent of kids never finish high school."},{"time":586000,"text":"And that had been covered up for a long time"},{"time":589000,"text":"because they always took the dropout rate as the number"},{"time":592000,"text":"who started in senior year and compared it to the number who finished senior year."},{"time":597000,"text":"Because they weren't tracking where the kids were before that."},{"time":599000,"text":"But most of the dropouts had taken place before that."},{"time":602000,"text":"They had to raise the stated dropout rate"},{"time":605000,"text":"as soon as that tracking was done"},{"time":607000,"text":"to over 30 percent."},{"time":609000,"text":"For minority kids, it's over 50 percent."},{"time":613000,"text":"And even if you graduate from high school,"},{"time":616000,"text":"if you're low-income,"},{"time":619000,"text":"you have less than a 25 percent chance of ever completing a college degree."},{"time":623000,"text":"If you're low-income in the United States,"},{"time":628000,"text":"you have a higher chance of going to jail"},{"time":632000,"text":"than you do of getting a four-year degree."},{"time":634000,"text":"And that doesn't seem entirely fair."}]},{"cues":[{"time":637000,"text":"So, how do you make education better?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":640000,"text":"Now, our foundation, for the last nine years, has invested in this."},{"time":644000,"text":"There's many people working on it."},{"time":647000,"text":"We've worked on small schools,"},{"time":650000,"text":"we've funded scholarships,"},{"time":652000,"text":"we've done things in libraries."},{"time":654000,"text":"A lot of these things had a good effect."},{"time":656000,"text":"But the more we looked at it, the more we realized that having great teachers"},{"time":659000,"text":"was the very key thing."},{"time":662000,"text":"And we hooked up with some people studying"},{"time":665000,"text":"how much variation is there between teachers,"},{"time":668000,"text":"between, say, the top quartile -- the very best --"},{"time":671000,"text":"and the bottom quartile."},{"time":673000,"text":"How much variation is there within a school or between schools?"},{"time":676000,"text":"And the answer is that these variations are absolutely unbelievable."},{"time":681000,"text":"A top quartile teacher will increase the performance of their class --"},{"time":686000,"text":"based on test scores --"},{"time":689000,"text":"by over 10 percent in a single year."},{"time":691000,"text":"What does that mean?"},{"time":692000,"text":"That means that if the entire U.S., for two years,"},{"time":695000,"text":"had top quartile teachers,"},{"time":698000,"text":"the entire difference between us and Asia would go away."},{"time":702000,"text":"Within four years we would be blowing everyone in the world away."}]},{"cues":[{"time":708000,"text":"So, it's simple. All you need are those top quartile teachers."},{"time":713000,"text":"And so you'd say, \"Wow, we should reward those people."},{"time":717000,"text":"We should retain those people."},{"time":720000,"text":"We should find out what they're doing and transfer that skill to other people.\""},{"time":723000,"text":"But I can tell you that absolutely is not happening today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":728000,"text":"What are the characteristics of this top quartile?"},{"time":731000,"text":"What do they look like?"},{"time":733000,"text":"You might think these must be very senior teachers."},{"time":736000,"text":"And the answer is no."},{"time":738000,"text":"Once somebody has taught for three years"},{"time":741000,"text":"their teaching quality does not change thereafter."},{"time":746000,"text":"The variation is very, very small."},{"time":749000,"text":"You might think these are people with master's degrees."},{"time":754000,"text":"They've gone back and they've gotten their Master's of Education."},{"time":757000,"text":"This chart takes four different factors"},{"time":760000,"text":"and says how much do they explain teaching quality."},{"time":763000,"text":"That bottom thing, which says there's no effect at all,"},{"time":766000,"text":"is a master's degree."}]},{"cues":[{"time":770000,"text":"Now, the way the pay system works is there's two things that are rewarded."},{"time":774000,"text":"One is seniority."},{"time":776000,"text":"Because your pay goes up and you vest into your pension."},{"time":779000,"text":"The second is giving extra money to people who get their master's degree."},{"time":782000,"text":"But it in no way is associated with being a better teacher."},{"time":785000,"text":"Teach for America: slight effect."},{"time":788000,"text":"For math teachers majoring in math there's a measurable effect."},{"time":792000,"text":"But, overwhelmingly, it's your past performance."},{"time":797000,"text":"There are some people who are very good at this."},{"time":800000,"text":"And we've done almost nothing"},{"time":803000,"text":"to study what that is"},{"time":806000,"text":"and to draw it in and to replicate it,"},{"time":809000,"text":"to raise the average capability --"},{"time":812000,"text":"or to encourage the people with it to stay in the system."}]},{"cues":[{"time":815000,"text":"You might say, \"Do the good teachers stay and the bad teacher's leave?\""},{"time":818000,"text":"The answer is, on average, the slightly better teachers leave the system."},{"time":821000,"text":"And it's a system with very high turnover."}]},{"cues":[{"time":825000,"text":"Now, there are a few places -- very few -- where great teachers are being made."},{"time":831000,"text":"A good example of one is a set of charter schools called KIPP."},{"time":836000,"text":"KIPP means Knowledge Is Power."},{"time":839000,"text":"It's an unbelievable thing."},{"time":842000,"text":"They have 66 schools -- mostly middle schools, some high schools --"},{"time":845000,"text":"and what goes on is great teaching."},{"time":849000,"text":"They take the poorest kids,"},{"time":852000,"text":"and over 96 percent of their high school graduates go to four-year colleges."},{"time":856000,"text":"And the whole spirit and attitude in those schools"},{"time":859000,"text":"is very different than in the normal public schools."},{"time":862000,"text":"They're team teaching. They're constantly improving their teachers."},{"time":866000,"text":"They're taking data, the test scores,"},{"time":869000,"text":"and saying to a teacher, \"Hey, you caused this amount of increase.\""},{"time":872000,"text":"They're deeply engaged in making teaching better."}]},{"cues":[{"time":876000,"text":"When you actually go and sit in one of these classrooms,"},{"time":879000,"text":"at first it's very bizarre."},{"time":882000,"text":"I sat down and I thought, \"What is going on?\""},{"time":885000,"text":"The teacher was running around, and the energy level was high."},{"time":888000,"text":"I thought, \"I'm in the sports rally or something."},{"time":891000,"text":"What's going on?\""},{"time":893000,"text":"And the teacher was constantly scanning to see which kids weren't paying attention,"},{"time":896000,"text":"which kids were bored,"},{"time":898000,"text":"and calling kids rapidly, putting things up on the board."},{"time":901000,"text":"It was a very dynamic environment,"},{"time":903000,"text":"because particularly in those middle school years -- fifth through eighth grade --"},{"time":906000,"text":"keeping people engaged and setting the tone"},{"time":909000,"text":"that everybody in the classroom needs to pay attention,"},{"time":912000,"text":"nobody gets to make fun of it or have the position of the kid who doesn't want to be there."},{"time":918000,"text":"Everybody needs to be involved."},{"time":920000,"text":"And so KIPP is doing it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":923000,"text":"How does that compare to a normal school?"},{"time":926000,"text":"Well, in a normal school, teachers aren't told how good they are."},{"time":930000,"text":"The data isn't gathered."},{"time":933000,"text":"In the teacher's contract,"},{"time":935000,"text":"it will limit the number of times the principal can come into the classroom --"},{"time":939000,"text":"sometimes to once per year."},{"time":941000,"text":"And they need advanced notice to do that."},{"time":944000,"text":"So imagine running a factory where you've got these workers,"},{"time":947000,"text":"some of them just making crap"},{"time":950000,"text":"and the management is told, \"Hey, you can only come down here once a year,"},{"time":954000,"text":"but you need to let us know, because we might actually fool you,"},{"time":956000,"text":"and try and do a good job in that one brief moment.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":960000,"text":"Even a teacher who wants to improve doesn't have the tools to do it."},{"time":965000,"text":"They don't have the test scores,"},{"time":967000,"text":"and there's a whole thing of trying to block the data."},{"time":970000,"text":"For example, New York passed a law"},{"time":973000,"text":"that said that the teacher improvement data could not be made available and used"},{"time":978000,"text":"in the tenure decision for the teachers."},{"time":982000,"text":"And so that's sort of working in the opposite direction."},{"time":985000,"text":"But I'm optimistic about this,"},{"time":987000,"text":"I think there are some clear things we can do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":991000,"text":"First of all, there's a lot more testing going on,"},{"time":995000,"text":"and that's given us the picture of where we are."},{"time":998000,"text":"And that allows us to understand who's doing it well,"},{"time":1002000,"text":"and call them out, and find out what those techniques are."},{"time":1005000,"text":"Of course, digital video is cheap now."},{"time":1008000,"text":"Putting a few cameras in the classroom"},{"time":1010000,"text":"and saying that things are being recorded on an ongoing basis"},{"time":1016000,"text":"is very practical in all public schools."},{"time":1018000,"text":"And so every few weeks teachers could sit down"},{"time":1021000,"text":"and say, \"OK, here's a little clip of something I thought I did well."},{"time":1024000,"text":"Here's a little clip of something I think I did poorly."},{"time":1027000,"text":"Advise me -- when this kid acted up, how should I have dealt with that?\""},{"time":1030000,"text":"And they could all sit and work together on those problems."},{"time":1034000,"text":"You can take the very best teachers and kind of annotate it,"},{"time":1038000,"text":"have it so everyone sees who is the very best at teaching this stuff."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1042000,"text":"You can take those great courses and make them available"},{"time":1044000,"text":"so that a kid could go out and watch the physics course, learn from that."},{"time":1049000,"text":"If you have a kid who's behind,"},{"time":1051000,"text":"you would know you could assign them that video to watch and review the concept."},{"time":1055000,"text":"And in fact, these free courses could not only be available just on the Internet,"},{"time":1059000,"text":"but you could make it so that DVDs were always available,"},{"time":1063000,"text":"and so anybody who has access to a DVD player can have the very best teachers."},{"time":1070000,"text":"And so by thinking of this as a personnel system,"},{"time":1075000,"text":"we can do it much better."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1077000,"text":"Now there's a book actually, about KIPP --"},{"time":1079000,"text":"the place that this is going on --"},{"time":1081000,"text":"that Jay Matthews, a news reporter, wrote -- called, \"Work Hard, Be Nice.\""},{"time":1086000,"text":"And I thought it was so fantastic."},{"time":1088000,"text":"It gave you a sense of what a good teacher does."},{"time":1092000,"text":"I'm going to send everyone here a free copy of this book."},{"time":1095000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1100000,"text":"Now, we put a lot of money into education,"},{"time":1103000,"text":"and I really think that education is the most important thing to get right"},{"time":1109000,"text":"for the country to have as strong a future as it should have."},{"time":1114000,"text":"In fact we have in the stimulus bill -- it's interesting --"},{"time":1116000,"text":"the House version actually had money in it for these data systems,"},{"time":1119000,"text":"and it was taken out in the Senate"},{"time":1121000,"text":"because there are people who are threatened by these things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1124000,"text":"But I -- I'm optimistic."},{"time":1126000,"text":"I think people are beginning to recognize how important this is,"},{"time":1130000,"text":"and it really can make a difference for millions of lives, if we get it right."},{"time":1137000,"text":"I only had time to frame those two problems."},{"time":1140000,"text":"There's a lot more problems like that --"},{"time":1142000,"text":"AIDS, pneumonia -- I can just see you're getting excited,"},{"time":1146000,"text":"just at the very name of these things."},{"time":1149000,"text":"And the skill sets required to tackle these things are very broad."},{"time":1154000,"text":"You know, the system doesn't naturally make it happen."},{"time":1157000,"text":"Governments don't naturally pick these things in the right way."},{"time":1162000,"text":"The private sector doesn't naturally put its resources into these things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1166000,"text":"So it's going to take brilliant people like you"},{"time":1169000,"text":"to study these things, get other people involved --"},{"time":1172000,"text":"and you're helping to come up with solutions."},{"time":1175000,"text":"And with that, I think there's some great things that will come out of it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1178000,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":1180000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}